# PLACEHOLDER — the vendored OpenSCAP (`oscap`) pin for the `scp-runner-scan` image.
#
# STATUS: STUB / not yet consumed (M13.3a follow-on). This increment (13.3a Build B) ships the
# TRIVY method only — see docs/proposals/airgap-cds-validate-promote.md §13.3 "Increment order:
# Trivy first, OpenSCAP second". OpenSCAP runner support (the `oscap` binary in the runner image,
# the XCCDF-rule-results → four-severity-count mapping, and the `openscap` method dispatch in
# apps/runner-scan/run.sh) is the SECOND half of 13.3a and lands with a real pin here.
#
# The file exists now so the vendoring discipline (tools/*/pin.env, mirroring tools/cosign +
# tools/skopeo) has its slot reserved and documented, exactly as ADR-0020 §1 / proposal §13.3
# describe ("Pins follow the tools/*/pin.env vendoring discipline: tools/trivy/pin.env,
# tools/openscap/pin.env"). NOTHING reads it until OpenSCAP runner support lands.

# The oscap release this pin WILL correspond to (unset — filled when OpenSCAP support lands).
OPENSCAP_PINNED_VERSION=
# The pinned oscap-carrying image digest (unset — filled when OpenSCAP support lands).
OPENSCAP_PINNED_IMAGE=
